.SH NAME
\*LSgVisualDrawingAreaInstallColormap \*O\(em Install a colormap for the VisualDrawingArea widget
.iX "SgVisualDrawingAreaInstallColormap"
.iX "VisualDrawingArea" "Visual Drawing Area"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sS
.iS
\&#include <Sgm/VisualDrawingA.h>
.sp \n(PDu
void SgVisualDrawingAreaInstallColormap (\*Vwidget\*L)
.ta .5i 1.5i
	Widget	\*Vwidget\*L;
.wH .fi
.iE
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
\*LSgVisualDrawingAreaInstallColormap\*O installs the colormap of an
\*LSgVisualDrawingArea\*O widget.  Normally it does this by adding the
widget's window to the WM_COLORMAP_WINDOWS property on the shell
containing the widget.  This causes the window manager to install the
colormap whenever the shell has focus.  (However, if the shell is marked
override_redirect, the widget calls \*LXInstallColormap(1X)\*O
directly in addition changing WM_COLORMAP_WINDOWS.  Some window
managers will reject such a change).
.P
There is no need to call \*LSgVisualDrawingAreaInstallColormap\*O if the
\*LSgNinstallColormap\*O is set, as this resource will automatically
set the WM_COLORMAP_WINDOWS property.  This call is intended for
providing more explicit control.
.P
To uninstall the colormap, call \*LSgVisualDrawingAreaUninstallColormap(3X)\*O.
.VL .75i 
.LI "\*Vwidget\*O"
Specifies the widget whose colormap is to be installed.
.LE 
.PP 
For a complete definition of VisualDrawingArea and its associated
resources, see
\*LSgVisualDrawingArea(3X)\*O.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the VisualDrawingArea widget ID.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.na
\*LSgVisualDrawingArea(3X)\*O, \*LSgVisualDrawingAreaInstallColormap(3X)\*O .
